(482, 'SCA-UA 1', 48, 2, 'Concepts in Social & Cultural Analysis', 'A gateway to all majors offered by SCA. Focuses on the core concepts that intersect the constituent programs of SCA: Africana Studies, American Studies, Asian/Pacific/ American Studies, Gender and Sexuality Studies, Latino Studies, and Metropolitan Studies. Surveys basic approaches to a range of significant analytical concepts (for example, property, work, technology, nature, popular culture, consumption, knowledge), each one considered within a two-week unit.', 4, '', 1, 0),
(483, 'SCA-UA 20', 48, 2, 'Strategies for Social & Cultural Analysis', 'Explores various research methodologies that scholars and practitioners employ to answer both historical and contemporary questions. Throughout the semester seminar participants are introduced to four broad categories of strategies for social and cultural analysis: historical analysis, particularly archival research; literary analysis, which deals primarily with critical analysis of texts; social science methods, focusing on the collection and interpretation of data and quantitative methods; and ethnography, along with other forms of fieldwork. In each of the four sections of the course, students grapple with both the theory and the application of the methodology being considered, and are encouraged to think carefully about which strategy or strategies are most appropriate for his or her own research projects. ', 4, '', 1, 0);
