(1257, 'MEDI-GA 1100', 127, 6, 'Proseminar in Medieval & Renaissance Studies', 'An introduction to the primary materials, reference works, journals, and research methodologies that pertain to the field of Medieval and Renaissance Studies together with an introduction to its sub-disciplines, including religion, psychology and philosophy, secular art and literature, architecture, historiography, economics and trade, science, translation studies, and the history of the book. The course is team taught.', 4, '', 1, 0),
