(4584, 'UGPH-GU 60', 504, 19, 'Undergraduate Experiential Learning in Global Publ', 'The global health undergraduate internship has a three-fold goal: It: 1) broadens the studentâ€™s exposure to public health issues, 2) facilitates opportunities for studentâ€™s to observe public health work and leadership in action, and 3) increases the studentâ€™s knowledge of specific career opportunities. The internship is a semester long course where the student engages in fieldwork (a minimum of 90 hours) and attends in-class seminar sessions. The integration of didactic and practice experiences provide the student with opportunities to critically reflect on the fieldwork experience, complete a public health project that is mutually beneficial to the student and the organization, and synthesize public health knowledge, skills, and attitudes. ', 4, '', 1, 0),
